      "description": "Offering a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six with individual throttle bodies. This unit remains mechanically robust; the high-pressure VANOS system is fully operational and the rear subframe has been reinforced to mitigate common floor-pan fatigue. The powertrain delivers a linear torque curve through a precise 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory limited-slip differential. Suspension kinematics are tight, featuring updated bushings and Bilstein dampers that maintain proper geometry under lateral load. Recent preventative maintenance includes a comprehensive cooling system refresh and rod bearing replacement, ensuring the high-revving internals are protected. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the drivetrain and chassis remain optimized for peak performance.",
